                                <p>Meaning of Rudram Sanatanam</p>
                                <h2>Understanding the profound significance of our name</h2>
                                <span class="separator"></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text">
                                <p><b>Rudram</b> refers to the divine aspect of Lord Shiva, the supreme consciousness that destroys ignorance and illuminates the path to liberation. The Rudram chant from the Yajurveda is one of the most powerful Vedic hymns, invoking the transformative energy of Shiva.  
</p>
                                <p><b>Sanatanam</b> means eternal, timeless, and everlasting. It represents the eternal dharma - the universal principles that have existed since time immemorial and will continue forever.</p>
                                
                                <p>Together, <b>Rudram Sanatanam</b> embodies the eternal divine consciousness that guides us toward spiritual awakening, inner transformation, and ultimate realization of our true nature.</p>
                            </div>
